text: Justin Omoregie (born 21 September 2003) is an Austrian professional footballer. He plays as midfielder for 2. Liga club FC Liefering. He also plays for the FC Salzburg U19 squad in the 2021-22 UEFA Youth League. ==Career== He started his career with SV Aspern. In 2011 he went on to the youthteam of First Vienna FC. In 2013 he went to FK Austria Wien. In 2017 he went to the Red Bull Salzburg Academy. In January 2021 he went to FC Liefering. His debut was in July 2021. He was in the starting team against SV Horn. In the 83rd minute he got a red card. Justin Omoregie at transfermarkt.de ==National team== He played for the Austria U16, U17 and U19 national teams. In September 2019 he played his first match for the U17 team versus Romania, in September 2021 he played for the U19 team versus Turkey. ==Career statistics== ===Club=== Club Season League Cup Continental Other Total Division Apps Goals Apps Goals Apps Goals Apps Goals Apps Goals Red Bull Salzburg 2022–23 Austrian Bundesliga 0 0 0 0 – 0 0 0 0 Liefering 2021–22 2.
